t-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Oil_Reserves.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 viewBox=%220 0 11 15%22 width=%2215%22 height=%2211%22%3E %3Cg id=%22magnify-clip%22 fill=%22%23fff%22 stroke=%22%23000%22%3E %3Cpath id=%22bigbox%22 d=%22M1.509 1.865h10.99v7.919h-10.99z%22/%3E %3Cpath id=%22smallbox%22 d=%22M-1.499 6.868h5.943v4.904h-5.943z%22/%3E %3C/g%3E %3C/svg%3E&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>World&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oil_reserves\" title=\"Oil reserves\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">oil reserves</a>, 2013.</div></div></div><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 402px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Reservespie.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Reservespie.png/400px-Reservespie.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"291\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Reservespie.png/600px-Reservespie.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Reservespie.png/800px-Reservespie.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"911\" data-file-height=\"663\" style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Reservespie.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 viewBox=%220 0 11 15%22 width=%2215%22 height=%2211%22%3E %3Cg id=%22magnify-clip%22 fill=%22%23fff%22 stroke=%22%23000%22%3E %3Cpath id=%22bigbox%22 d=%22M1.509 1.865h10.99v7.919h-10.99z%22/%3E %3Cpath id=%22smallbox%22 d=%22M-1.499 6.868h5.943v4.904h-5.943z%22/%3E %3C/g%3E %3C/svg%3E&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>The distribution of oil and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_natural_gas_proven_reserves\" title=\"List of countries by natural gas proven reserves\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">gas reserves</a>&nbsp;among the world\'s 50 largest oil companies. The reserves of the privately owned companies are grouped together. The oil produced by the \"supermajor\" companies accounts for less than 15% of the total world supply. Over 80% of the world\'s reserves of oil and natural gas are controlled by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_oil_company\" title=\"National oil company\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">national oil companies</a>. Of the world\'s 20 largest oil companies, 15 are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State-owned_enterprise\" title=\"State-owned enterprise\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">state-owned oil companies</a>.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<b>petroleum industry</b>, also known as the&nbsp;<b>oil industry</b>&nbsp;or the&nbsp;<b>oil patch</b>, includes the global processes of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrocarbon_exploration\" title=\"Hydrocarbon exploration\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">exploration</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extraction_of_petroleum\" title=\"Extraction of petroleum\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">extraction</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oil_refinery\" title=\"Oil refinery\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">refining</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum_transport\" title=\"Petroleum transport\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">transporting</a>&nbsp;(often by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oil_tanker\" title=\"Oil tanker\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">oil tankers</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pipeline_transport\" title=\"Pipeline transport\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pipelines</a>), and marketing of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_crude_oil_products\" title=\"List of crude oil products\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">petroleum products</a>. The largest volume products of the industry are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_oil\" title=\"Fuel oil\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fuel oil</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gasoline\" title=\"Gasoline\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">gasoline</a>(petrol). Petroleum (oil) is also the raw material for many&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petrochemical\" title=\"Petrochemical\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chemical products</a>, including&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmaceutical_drug\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pharmaceutical drug\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pharmaceuticals</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solvent\" title=\"Solvent\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">solvents</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fertilizer\" title=\"Fertilizer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fertilizers</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pesticide\" title=\"Pesticide\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pesticides</a>, synthetic fragrances, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plastic\" title=\"Plastic\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">plastics</a>. The extreme monetary value of oil and its products has led to it being known as \"black gold\". The industry is usually divided into three major components:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upstream_(petroleum_industry)\" title=\"Upstream (petroleum industry)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">upstream</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midstream\" title=\"Midstream\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">midstream</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Downstream_(petroleum_industry)\" title=\"\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">downstream</a>. Midstream operations are often included in the downstream category.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Petroleum is vital to many industries, and is of importance to the maintenance of industrial&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilization\" title=\"Civilization\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">civilization</a>in its current configuration, and thus is a critical concern for many nations. Oil accounts for a large percentage of the world’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energy_consumption\" title=\"Energy consumption\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">energy consumption</a>, ranging from a low of 32% for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe\" title=\"Europe\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Europe</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asia\" title=\"Asia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Asia</a>, to a high of 53% for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_East\" title=\"Middle East\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Middle East</a>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Other geographic regions\' consumption patterns are as follows:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_America\" title=\"South America\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_America\" title=\"Central America\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Central America</a>&nbsp;(44%),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Africa\" title=\"Africa\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Africa</a>&nbsp;(41%), and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America\" title=\"North America\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">North America</a>&nbsp;(40%). The world consumes 30 billion&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrel_(unit)\" title=\"Barrel (unit)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">barrels</a>&nbsp;(4.8&nbsp;km³) of oil per year, with developed nations being the largest consumers. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">United States</a>&nbsp;consumed 25% of the oil produced in 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum_industry#cite_note-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;The production, distribution, refining, and retailing of petroleum taken as a whole represents the world\'s largest industry in terms of dollar value.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Governments such as the United States government provide a heavy public&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energy_subsidies#Impact_of_fossil_fuel_subsidies\" title=\"Energy subsidies\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">subsidy to petroleum companies</a>, with major tax breaks at virtually every stage of oil exploration and extraction, including the costs of oil field leases and drilling equipment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-nytimes.com_2-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum_industry#cite_note-nytimes.com-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In recent years, hydraulic fracturing has moved to the forefront of the industry as this new technology plays an extremely crucial and controversial role in new methods of oil extraction.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum_industry#cite_note-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup></p>', 'nbsp,companies,industry,largest,products,petroleum,world\'s,reserves,many,world,extraction,United,with,America,downstream', 'PA', '2018-09-15 10:07:04', '', 1, NULL),
